FBIS4-65231 "drweu093_q_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-093 Daily Report 12 May 1994 TURKEY Athens Warned on Extending Territorial Waters Athens Warned on Extending Territorial Waters TA1205161694 Ankara ANATOLIA in French 1550 GMT 12 May 94 TA1205161694 Ankara ANATOLIA French BFN [Text] Ankara, 12 May 1994 (A.A.) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat Ataman declared on Thursday [12 May] that Athens' desire to extend its territorial waters to 12 nautical miles is unacceptable. Until 1936, Greece had limited its territorial waters to 3 miles. After the Montreux Convention on the straits, it extended its territorial waters to 6 nautical miles. Turkey claims that Athens' extension of its territorial waters to 12 nautical miles will be considered a declaration of war. Greek Foreign Ministry spokesman Konstandinos Bikas [name as received] affirmed that it is Greece's sovereign right to extend its waters to 12 nautical miles.
